1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,263
Most AI tutors are excellent at giving answers.

2
00:00:03,263 --> 00:00:07,909
But a correct explanation can still leave the wrong mental model untouched.

3
00:00:07,909 --> 00:00:13,177
Hingewise starts one step earlier: it asks you to explain what you think is happening.

4
00:00:13,177 --> 00:00:18,869
In this example, the learner believes summer happens because Earth moves closer to the Sun.

5
00:00:18,869 --> 00:00:27,037
Hingewise sends that explanation to GPT-5.6—not to grade the learner,
but to reconstruct the reasoning behind the answer.

6
00:00:27,037 --> 00:00:33,031
It preserves what is already sound: sunlight heats Earth, and distance can affect intensity.

7
00:00:33,031 --> 00:00:39,827
Then it identifies the earliest wrong turn—the hidden hinge—
the assumption that distance controls the seasons.

8
00:00:39,827 --> 00:00:41,500
Here is the key interaction.

9
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:46,206
Switch from Before to After, and Hingewise replaces only that hinge.

10
00:00:46,206 --> 00:00:51,970
The reasoning realigns around Earth’s tilt, the angle of sunlight,
and the length of each day.

11
00:00:51,970 --> 00:00:56,626
The correction becomes visible instead of disappearing inside a chat response.

12
00:00:56,626 --> 00:01:00,347
Hingewise also explains why the original belief felt reasonable.

13
00:01:00,347 --> 00:01:09,124
Then it asks for a prediction before revealing the repair: if distance causes seasons,
should Australia and Canada have summer at the same time?

14
00:01:09,124 --> 00:01:11,780
The contradiction creates a useful surprise.

15
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:16,507
A final transfer question asks the learner to apply the repaired model again.

16
00:01:16,507 --> 00:01:23,053
As learning continues, learners can revisit earlier analyses
to see how their thinking changes over time.

17
00:01:23,053 --> 00:01:26,001
I used Codex as the primary build partner.

18
00:01:26,001 --> 00:01:36,828
It checked the current requirements, explored product directions, implemented the responsive interface
and GPT-5.6 integration, diagnosed problems, wrote integration tests, and prepared the deployment and submission materials.

19
00:01:36,828 --> 00:01:46,902
My role was to test each version as a learner, considering both the first experience
and how it felt over repeated use.

20
00:01:46,902 --> 00:01:54,703
I identified friction and suggested improvements that made the learning process clearer,
more continuous, and more useful over time.

21
00:01:54,703 --> 00:01:59,671
GPT-5.6 is the reasoning engine behind every live analysis.

22
00:01:59,671 --> 00:02:06,217
Using strict Structured Outputs, it transforms a free-form explanation into a before-and-after reasoning trace,
a targeted repair challenge, and a transfer check.

23
00:02:06,217 --> 00:02:12,800
That’s Hingewise: find the belief behind the mistake,
change the hinge, and watch the reasoning realign.
